  "question_id" : 52112639,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/52112639/how-can-the-object-class-be-a-super-class-of-subclasses",
  "title" : "How can the Object class be a super class of subclasses?",
  "body" : "<p><strong>Fact 1:</strong></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Java does not support multiple inheritance.</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p><strong>Fact 2:</strong></p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Object is a superclass of all other classes</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>If I have a class <code>Parent</code> and a class <code>Child</code> which is inheriting the class <code>Parent</code>:</p>\n\n<pre><code>class Parent {\n\n}\n\nclass Child extends Parent {\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>In this case, how will the class <code>Child</code> inherit the <code>Object</code> class, if Java does not support multiple inheritance?</p>\n\n<p>How is the relationship between these three defined?</p>\n\n<p><strong>Option 1:</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qw1Jq.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/qw1Jq.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>Option 2:</strong></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/6ZwPj.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/6ZwPj.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
}